cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about instance-level video segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a novel approach that relies on attention cues, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also achieves state-of-the-art performance on a video dataset, which involves multimedia analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper optimizes a loss function to assign instance-specific penalties, which involves optimization techniques, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category as well.
